You don't have to go this far
to protect them.

275
00:19:03,425 --> 00:19:05,945
I'm not protecting anyone.
It's really mine.

276
00:19:06,165 --> 00:19:09,424
Uh... but how could it be yours?

277
00:19:09,425 --> 00:19:11,695
Since when did you
even glance at this?

278
00:19:13,785 --> 00:19:16,875
Well... I'm planning
to write a BL novel

279
00:19:17,885 --> 00:19:19,525
to pay off the debt.

280
00:19:22,635 --> 00:19:24,755
BL novel? What is it?

281
00:19:25,045 --> 00:19:28,784
Come on.
It's boys' love romance novel.

282
00:19:28,785 --> 00:19:31,785
You can't write that, Dad.
That's not you.

283
00:19:32,305 --> 00:19:34,545
I can. I just need some practice.

284
00:19:34,785 --> 00:19:39,225
Dad, a great writer like you,
taking on this genre?

285
00:19:39,745 --> 00:19:41,705
People are really
into it these days.

286
00:19:42,065 --> 00:19:44,745
And if it sells,
the money's decent.

287
00:19:45,275 --> 00:19:46,275
Please don't, Dad.

288
00:19:47,235 --> 00:19:48,504
There has to be a better way.

289
00:19:48,505 --> 00:19:51,905
You haven't written a novel
in over thirty years.

290
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:55,265
You think you can just
pick it back up now?

291
00:19:55,505 --> 00:19:57,265
I said I can, didn't I?

292
00:20:00,145 --> 00:20:01,465
Just sell the place, Dad.

293
00:20:05,425 --> 00:20:07,445
Sun, how did you know about this?

294
00:20:07,945 --> 00:20:09,225
I told him.

295
00:20:09,985 --> 00:20:11,145
Why did you?

296
00:20:11,465 --> 00:20:14,425
He is his son and your kid brother.

297
00:20:14,815 --> 00:20:16,825
He's family.

298
00:20:17,185 --> 00:20:19,265
He has every right
to know what's going on.

299
00:20:23,505 --> 00:20:26,024
Dad, if you really can't hold on,

300
00:20:26,025 --> 00:20:29,105
I think...
you'd better sell the orphanage.

301
00:20:29,225 --> 00:20:31,325
It'll relieve you of this stress.

302
00:20:31,785 --> 00:20:32,985
I'm not selling.

303
00:20:33,705 --> 00:20:36,985
Then you'll need to open up
for more donations.

304
00:20:37,165 --> 00:20:39,784
Or reach out to former residents
with the means to help.

305
00:20:39,785 --> 00:20:41,145
Anything that can cover the debt.

306
00:20:41,545 --> 00:20:43,184
That could work.

307
00:20:43,185 --> 00:20:46,905
We've never once told them
that we're struggling.

308
00:20:47,185 --> 00:20:51,185
If we put the word out,
I'm sure they would want to help.

309
00:20:51,505 --> 00:20:52,505
No.

310
00:20:53,305 --> 00:20:56,705
They have their own lives now.

311
00:20:57,015 --> 00:21:00,905
I've raised these kids
hoping to see them thrive.

312
00:21:01,005 --> 00:21:02,945
Not to have them repay anything.

313
00:21:05,705 --> 00:21:07,835
Grandmother, please sit down.

314
00:21:08,025 --> 00:21:09,825
Come, come. Right there.

315
00:21:09,865 --> 00:21:12,785
Dad, we can't just keep
going like this.

316
00:21:13,475 --> 00:21:14,785
You must do something.

317
00:21:15,345 --> 00:21:17,585
I'm working on it.

318
00:21:17,615 --> 00:21:18,985
The bank won't wait for that.

319
00:21:19,565 --> 00:21:21,735
Sun, don't push him like that.

320
00:21:21,775 --> 00:21:23,505
I'm just laying out the facts.

321
00:21:26,545 --> 00:21:28,625
Dad, I don't see any other way.

322
00:21:28,995 --> 00:21:32,145
The best option now is to sell.
Plain and simple.

323
00:21:32,585 --> 00:21:33,585
No.

324
00:21:35,305 --> 00:21:36,584
Selling is not an option.

325
00:21:36,585 --> 00:21:38,025
Why not?

326
00:21:42,025 --> 00:21:43,145
You may eat.

327
00:21:51,465 --> 00:21:53,105
All right. Enjoy.

328
00:21:54,025 --> 00:21:55,145
Luang (honorific), sir.

329
00:21:55,945 --> 00:21:58,785
What is it, Phi Boonma?

330
00:22:00,455 --> 00:22:02,785
Could I trouble you
to keep an eye on Tone?

331
00:22:03,025 --> 00:22:04,425
Just through the afternoon.

332
00:22:05,005 --> 00:22:06,865
I'll pick him up
when I'm done with work.

333
00:22:06,895 --> 00:22:08,215
My wife just passed.

334
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:10,425
There's no one to look after him.

335
00:22:10,745 --> 00:22:12,945
Of course. I'll take care of him.

336
00:22:13,985 --> 00:22:15,025
Thank you, Luang.

337
00:22:15,385 --> 00:22:17,825
All right, Tone. Greet him properly.

338
00:22:18,155 --> 00:22:19,155
Hmm.

339
00:22:19,825 --> 00:22:22,305
Come, just in time for a meal.

340
00:22:23,855 --> 00:22:26,424
Luang, the villagers
raised this sum.

341
00:22:26,425 --> 00:22:27,625
Please keep it.

342
00:22:30,735 --> 00:22:31,745
It's a lot of money.

343
00:22:32,345 --> 00:22:34,065
I can't.

344
00:22:35,125 --> 00:22:36,304
Please take it.

345
00:22:36,305 --> 00:22:39,185
We understand your dedication
to care for these children.

346
00:22:39,465 --> 00:22:41,065
We all want to do our part.

347
00:22:41,305 --> 00:22:44,305
You could purchase
the adjoining land

348
00:22:44,365 --> 00:22:46,715
and build a proper house for them.

349
00:22:47,085 --> 00:22:50,625
So they don't have to
put up with cramped living.

350
00:22:52,545 --> 00:22:54,075
Please accept it, Luang (honorific).

351
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:59,745
I don't know how to...
thank you on behalf of the children.

352
00:23:00,215 --> 00:23:03,185
We're happy to support
your dedication.

353
00:23:03,995 --> 00:23:07,425
I promise I will use this land

354
00:23:08,015 --> 00:23:10,505
for the good of these children.
Always.

355
00:23:11,215 --> 00:23:13,225
The land isn't ours to sell

356
00:23:13,845 --> 00:23:16,824
because the villagers
donated their money

357
00:23:16,825 --> 00:23:18,625
to find a home for children in need.

358
00:23:19,225 --> 00:23:21,705
Selling it
would betray that purpose.

359
00:23:22,085 --> 00:23:23,025
It's not for sale.

360
00:23:23,026 --> 00:23:24,585
But that was so long ago, Dad.

361
00:23:24,865 --> 00:23:26,664
The donors are all gone now.

362
00:23:26,665 --> 00:23:28,105
I'm still here.

363
00:23:32,505 --> 00:23:34,985
I will never compromise
my grandfather's vision.

364
00:23:37,245 --> 00:23:40,225
Honestly, I don't agree
with selling it either.

365
00:23:40,505 --> 00:23:41,945
Stay out of this, Sun.

366
00:23:42,745 --> 00:23:44,425
We'll find our own way.

367
00:23:46,625 --> 00:23:48,065
Then I have nothing more to say.

368
00:23:51,465 --> 00:23:52,865
Thank you for coming.

369
00:23:53,675 --> 00:23:56,105
I'll head out then. Back to work.

370
00:23:58,745 --> 00:23:59,785
Bye, Dad.

371
00:24:10,445 --> 00:24:13,585
That's Sun for you.

372
00:24:19,735 --> 00:24:23,365
Nevertheless, keep this
from Save and Snow.

373
00:24:24,265 --> 00:24:25,745
They'll only worry.

374
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:35,274
Don't get there. Come on, quick.

375
00:24:35,275 --> 00:24:37,185
Save. Hey, Save.

376
00:24:38,005 --> 00:24:39,125
Pass it over.

377
00:24:39,905 --> 00:24:41,025
Save, pass. Come on.

378
00:24:44,655 --> 00:24:45,455
Ow.

379
00:24:45,485 --> 00:24:46,745
- Oh, come on.
- Aw.

380
00:24:47,045 --> 00:24:48,545
- What?
- Hate the game, guys.

381
00:24:48,565 --> 00:24:49,095
Sorry.

382
00:24:49,115 --> 00:24:50,785
- Unbelievable.
- Let's go. Go.

383
00:24:50,815 --> 00:24:51,815
Try harder.

384
00:24:52,715 --> 00:24:54,105
Nice. Jang, that was nice.

385
00:25:00,675 --> 00:25:03,425
- Heh.
- Enough.

386
00:25:04,955 --> 00:25:06,225
Dude, it wasn't my fault.

387
00:25:06,925 --> 00:25:07,925
Hey.

388
00:25:08,945 --> 00:25:10,205
- Ron.
- Oh, hey.

389
00:25:10,225 --> 00:25:12,245
- Hey.
- Hey.

390
00:25:12,725 --> 00:25:14,464
Ron, you gaming tonight?

391
00:25:14,465 --> 00:25:15,985
Sure, nine o'clock, yeah?

392
00:25:16,265 --> 00:25:18,495
- Don't go dark on us again.
- He will.

393
00:25:18,515 --> 00:25:20,105
All the time, this guy.

394
00:25:20,535 --> 00:25:21,505
Never.

395
00:25:21,506 --> 00:25:22,945
- Never what?
- Never?

396
00:25:23,115 --> 00:25:25,385
- Haha.
- Haha.

397
00:25:26,365 --> 00:25:28,385
So stuffed, man.

398
00:25:28,645 --> 00:25:29,645
Yeah, up to here.

399
00:25:30,305 --> 00:25:31,505
Can't do soccer now. Too full.

400
00:25:31,545 --> 00:25:33,265
- So full.
- Still full.

401
00:25:34,825 --> 00:25:35,825
Ugh.

402
00:25:36,275 --> 00:25:39,224
- Hey, Jang, Pheem, free tickets.
- You got them?

403
00:25:39,225 --> 00:25:40,625
- Hold on.
- Free to what?

404
00:25:40,655 --> 00:25:41,705
Go ask him.

405
00:25:43,035 --> 00:25:44,075
We need to talk.

406
00:25:45,625 --> 00:25:46,704
I want to go to class.

407
00:25:46,705 --> 00:25:48,025
Class? You?

408
00:25:48,745 --> 00:25:49,745
Yeah.

409
00:25:51,745 --> 00:25:52,745
Just talk to me.

410
00:25:54,625 --> 00:25:55,785
Come on.

411
00:25:57,975 --> 00:25:59,015
What's wrong with you?

412
00:25:59,505 --> 00:26:00,625
Nothing.

413
00:26:00,905 --> 00:26:02,105
You're not yourself.

414
00:26:03,025 --> 00:26:04,025
I am myself.

415
00:26:04,325 --> 00:26:05,905
You said you wouldn't act weird.

416
00:26:09,945 --> 00:26:11,225
You think it's that easy?

417
00:26:11,945 --> 00:26:13,175
Us the way we were?

418
00:26:13,995 --> 00:26:15,745
After you told me you liked me?

419
00:26:16,625 --> 00:26:17,965
You hate me now?

420
00:26:18,325 --> 00:26:19,325
No.

421
00:26:20,145 --> 00:26:22,025
I make you feel uncomfortable?

422
00:26:22,405 --> 00:26:23,405
Huh.

423
00:26:26,895 --> 00:26:28,585
Fine. I'm sorry.

424
00:26:29,065 --> 00:26:30,785
I told you, stop apologizing.

425
00:26:31,145 --> 00:26:32,145
This is on me.

426
00:26:32,755 --> 00:26:34,185
I ruined everything.

427
00:26:34,945 --> 00:26:37,145
From now on, I won't be around you.

428
00:26:58,915 --> 00:26:59,985
Whew.

429
00:27:29,905 --> 00:27:31,465
"1"

430
00:28:19,505 --> 00:28:20,865
Oh, hi.

431
00:28:21,145 --> 00:28:24,065
Hey, Save. Humor me this.

432
00:28:24,745 --> 00:28:27,065
What's it like
when a boy likes another boy?

433
00:28:27,715 --> 00:28:28,725
What kind of question is that?

434
00:28:28,745 --> 00:28:31,224
Well, I'm writing a BL novel.

435
00:28:31,225 --> 00:28:33,225
- Ha? A BL novel?
- Yeah.

436
00:28:33,715 --> 00:28:35,065
You got nothing else?

437
00:28:35,465 --> 00:28:38,345
I just want to try.
Help me out a little.

438
00:28:38,625 --> 00:28:42,224
Tell me how it feels
when two boys like each other.

439
00:28:42,225 --> 00:28:45,305
Oy, you got the wrong boy.
How should I know?

440
00:28:45,335 --> 00:28:46,734
I'm not into boys.

441
00:28:46,735 --> 00:28:49,065
Ow, you're a teenager.

442
00:28:49,345 --> 00:28:52,664
Some of your friends
may be like that. Right?

443
00:28:52,665 --> 00:28:54,825
None. Just don't write it, Grandpa.

444
00:28:55,105 --> 00:28:56,345
Drop it. Quit.

445
00:28:56,705 --> 00:28:58,625
You can't pull off a BL novel.

446
00:29:00,515 --> 00:29:01,515
Huh.

447
00:29:02,785 --> 00:29:03,785
Why got mad?

448
00:29:13,315 --> 00:29:14,315
Okay.

449
00:29:17,555 --> 00:29:19,305
Yeah, good.

450
00:29:20,905 --> 00:29:24,185
Mart, I don't think
Dad can write that novel.

451
00:29:24,385 --> 00:29:26,305
Hmm. That's what I figured.

452
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:29,785
So what do we do then?

453
00:29:30,765 --> 00:29:31,765
Hmm.

454
00:29:32,745 --> 00:29:34,745
We could try selling something.

455
00:29:34,895 --> 00:29:37,285
Who's got money in this economy?

456
00:29:37,335 --> 00:29:38,505
Well.

457
00:29:39,535 --> 00:29:42,625
We gotta come up with
things they want to buy.

458
00:29:43,305 --> 00:29:44,305
Like what?

459
00:29:44,335 --> 00:29:46,345
Help me think.

460
00:29:46,395 --> 00:29:47,905
I'm helping and thinking.

461
00:29:50,445 --> 00:29:53,685
Even if we figure it out,
who knows if we can make them?

462
00:29:54,215 --> 00:29:55,465
That's the question.

463
00:29:56,875 --> 00:29:58,705
Oh, Grandmother.

464
00:29:59,025 --> 00:30:01,385
Oh, stop, stop.

465
00:30:01,885 --> 00:30:04,345
Hmm. You're at it again.

466
00:30:07,295 --> 00:30:09,385
Sanae Chan, The Royal Recipe.

467
00:30:13,635 --> 00:30:15,104
Phi Sorn. Phi Sorn.

468
00:30:15,105 --> 00:30:16,625
Yeah? What is it?

469
00:30:17,255 --> 00:30:21,025
Hmph. Are you deaf?
Didn't you hear me?

470
00:30:21,725 --> 00:30:25,545
Grandmother, thank you.

471
00:30:25,645 --> 00:30:29,865
You really came through for us.
Thank you.

472
00:30:36,485 --> 00:30:37,485
What?

473
00:30:39,515 --> 00:30:42,185
Oh, now it just clicks.

474
00:30:43,385 --> 00:30:45,184
Dad used to tell me

475
00:30:45,185 --> 00:30:47,334
that when Grandmother was young,

476
00:30:47,335 --> 00:30:50,025
she studied confectionery
at the palace.

477
00:30:50,435 --> 00:30:54,505
These recipes are
over a hundred years old.

478
00:30:58,885 --> 00:30:59,885
Ah-ha.

479
00:31:01,655 --> 00:31:02,785
Now sift.

480
00:31:08,235 --> 00:31:09,025
All right.

481
00:31:09,145 --> 00:31:10,265
Oh, hmph.

482
00:31:12,295 --> 00:31:15,245
Oh, no. Like this.

483
00:31:15,365 --> 00:31:17,625
Just tap.

484
00:31:17,765 --> 00:31:19,345
- I see.
- Be patient.

485
00:31:19,365 --> 00:31:21,784
Or it'll be all over the place.

486
00:31:21,785 --> 00:31:22,875
- Got it.
- Yeah.

487
00:31:25,095 --> 00:31:26,095
Okay.

488
00:31:39,885 --> 00:31:40,945
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

489
00:31:42,665 --> 00:31:44,215
Okay. Put this in.

490
00:31:44,255 --> 00:31:45,255
100 grams.

491
00:31:47,535 --> 00:31:48,535
Hold on.

492
00:31:58,965 --> 00:32:00,905
And this.

493
00:32:05,835 --> 00:32:09,185
Now... mix well.

494
00:32:26,655 --> 00:32:29,225
- Phi Sorn, nice color, see?
- Oh, wow.

495
00:32:31,115 --> 00:32:32,665
- It's coming together.
- Yes, yes.

496
00:32:32,695 --> 00:32:33,705
Get the tray.

497
00:32:33,725 --> 00:32:34,725
Here.

498
00:32:36,755 --> 00:32:38,185
Okay. Ready.

499
00:32:45,825 --> 00:32:47,025
Twenty-three.

500
00:32:50,295 --> 00:32:51,425
That's ten.

501
00:33:02,885 --> 00:33:03,885
Here. Here.

502
00:33:04,895 --> 00:33:06,425
- Nice, huh?
- Here...

503
00:33:10,225 --> 00:33:12,664
Oh, forgive its shape for now.

504
00:33:12,665 --> 00:33:14,465
Let's get the flavor right first.

505
00:33:28,535 --> 00:33:29,945
Oh, no. Grandmother.

506
00:33:30,715 --> 00:33:31,715
Huh.

507
00:33:32,155 --> 00:33:35,765
Um. Didn't we get the right flavor?

508
00:33:36,105 --> 00:33:39,385
I guess it's really bad
that she spits it out.

509
00:33:39,515 --> 00:33:40,635
Oh, Phi Sorn.

510
00:33:40,715 --> 00:33:42,865
I did say it tasted strange.

511
00:33:45,715 --> 00:33:47,745
I will try again, Grandmother.

512
00:34:15,035 --> 00:34:16,465
Hey, Guy.

513
00:34:17,235 --> 00:34:18,235
- Guy.
- Oh.

514
00:34:27,135 --> 00:34:28,475
Didn't he see me?

515
00:34:28,495 --> 00:34:30,404
He saw me, yeah?
He looked right at me.

516
00:34:30,405 --> 00:34:31,745
- He did.
- Yeah, man.

517
00:34:51,715 --> 00:34:52,825
Uh... oops.

518
00:34:53,525 --> 00:34:57,705
Phi Sorn, what a mess.

519
00:34:57,735 --> 00:34:58,385
Um...

520
00:34:58,386 --> 00:35:01,075
- Phi Sorn.
- It happens. No big deal.

521
00:35:01,105 --> 00:35:03,305
- Be careful.
- I'll just try again.

522
00:35:03,325 --> 00:35:06,385
- It's a big bowl there.
- I don't want to break the yolk.

523
00:35:06,405 --> 00:35:07,185
Ugh.

524
00:35:07,186 --> 00:35:08,425
- I'm trying, okay?
- Oh?

525
00:35:11,265 --> 00:35:13,285
We haven't made any money yet.

526
00:35:13,305 --> 00:35:14,985
- But eggs are out.
- Mom, Dad.

527
00:35:15,015 --> 00:35:16,844
What is all this mess?

528
00:35:16,845 --> 00:35:19,185
Your mom wants to
make sweets to sell.

529
00:35:19,295 --> 00:35:21,504
What? Selling sweets?

530
00:35:21,505 --> 00:35:22,625
That's food, right?

531
00:35:23,545 --> 00:35:26,665
Aw... a little encouragement
would be nice.

532
00:35:27,865 --> 00:35:29,385
I hope nobody gets food poisoning.

533
00:35:29,675 --> 00:35:33,104
You. Wipe that off.

534
00:35:33,105 --> 00:35:35,465
- There you go.
- Oh, Dad.

535
00:35:52,665 --> 00:35:56,815
Here. Check this out.
Hehe.

536
00:36:22,385 --> 00:36:23,585
Ugh.

537
00:36:23,925 --> 00:36:25,025
Hmm.

538
00:37:05,465 --> 00:37:06,465
Huh.

539
00:38:17,985 --> 00:38:18,985
Hmm?

540
00:38:25,425 --> 00:38:26,825
Is it good now?

541
00:38:29,145 --> 00:38:30,625
- Heh.
- Ha!

542
00:38:31,665 --> 00:38:35,305
We did it, Phi Sorn. We got it.

543
00:38:35,335 --> 00:38:36,335
Eh-haha.

544
00:38:40,115 --> 00:38:42,025
I did great.

545
00:38:50,605 --> 00:38:51,605
Careful.

546
00:38:52,265 --> 00:38:55,025
- Oh, wow.
- Wow.

547
00:38:58,055 --> 00:38:59,615
Go ahead. Try some.

548
00:39:00,315 --> 00:39:01,384
- Yes.
- Yeah.

549
00:39:01,385 --> 00:39:02,635
Slow down. Slow down.

550
00:39:02,655 --> 00:39:05,365
No need to fight over them.
They're all good.

551
00:39:08,675 --> 00:39:11,105
Heck. Heck.

552
00:39:12,005 --> 00:39:14,305
Heck. Heck.

553
00:39:14,865 --> 00:39:17,105
Mom, what did you give us?

554
00:39:17,505 --> 00:39:18,785
Dirt mixed with sugar?

555
00:39:19,555 --> 00:39:20,555
Ow.

556
00:39:21,765 --> 00:39:23,445
A sweet is supposed to be sweet.

557
00:39:23,645 --> 00:39:25,545
If it's bland,
can you call it a sweet?

558
00:39:25,885 --> 00:39:27,465
Let's go find some water.

559
00:39:31,425 --> 00:39:32,425
Hmph.

560
00:39:34,385 --> 00:39:35,545
Is it that bad?

561
00:39:35,915 --> 00:39:36,915
Mm-hmm.

562
00:39:37,585 --> 00:39:39,265
The kids just don't
have the palate.

563
00:39:39,585 --> 00:39:43,025
Royal palace confectionery
isn't for everyone.

564
00:39:44,055 --> 00:39:45,055
Hmph.

565
00:39:45,905 --> 00:39:46,985
Really.

566
00:39:50,885 --> 00:39:52,345
Have a taste, Khun (honorific) On.

567
00:39:53,225 --> 00:39:54,225
Hmm.

568
00:40:08,185 --> 00:40:10,305
Throat-burning sweet, Khun Mart.

569
00:40:10,965 --> 00:40:11,965
Really?

570
00:40:12,425 --> 00:40:13,425
It is.

571
00:40:16,665 --> 00:40:18,145
I can't get it down.

572
00:40:28,345 --> 00:40:29,345
Water...

573
00:40:30,395 --> 00:40:32,145
Here, water. Water.

574
00:40:40,455 --> 00:40:43,914
Can I be honest with you?

575
00:40:43,915 --> 00:40:47,024
Yes, please. I need the feedback.

576
00:40:47,025 --> 00:40:49,505
It's very rough going down,
Khun Mart.

577
00:40:50,145 --> 00:40:52,145
It's sticky. Can't swallow it.

578
00:40:52,905 --> 00:40:55,665
I'm sorry. I really can't take it.

579
00:41:10,325 --> 00:41:11,465
Have some water.

580
00:41:14,425 --> 00:41:15,585
So how is it?

581
00:41:15,615 --> 00:41:18,345
Hmm. I think the recipe needs
a bit of tweaking.

582
00:41:19,505 --> 00:41:20,625
Yeah...

583
00:41:20,815 --> 00:41:23,615
You used to make sweets, Khun Phon.
Could you advise me?

584
00:41:23,775 --> 00:41:24,775
Of course.

585
00:41:25,285 --> 00:41:28,745
Hmm... have you ever tried
Japanese sweets?

586
00:41:28,935 --> 00:41:30,464
The texture is much smoother.

587
00:41:30,465 --> 00:41:32,344
And the sweetness isn't as sharp.

588
00:41:32,345 --> 00:41:35,505
You can apply that to your recipe.

589
00:41:36,065 --> 00:41:38,505
Really? How would I go about that?

590
00:42:11,275 --> 00:42:12,795
Is something the matter, Grandpa?

591
00:42:13,805 --> 00:42:16,785
Snow, will you read this?

592
00:42:17,465 --> 00:42:18,465
What is it?

593
00:42:19,685 --> 00:42:20,825
BL novel.

594
00:42:21,985 --> 00:42:23,105
Ump...

595
00:42:23,665 --> 00:42:24,985
You wrote this?

596
00:42:25,655 --> 00:42:26,655
Mm-hmm.

597
00:42:27,665 --> 00:42:30,425
Awesome. That's my grandpa.

598
00:42:30,455 --> 00:42:31,455
Good.

599
00:42:58,825 --> 00:43:01,625
"Hew"? What does it mean?

600
00:43:01,945 --> 00:43:04,024
That word is pronounced "wae."

601
00:43:04,025 --> 00:43:05,745
Hor-wor-ae, Wae.

602
00:43:07,385 --> 00:43:08,624
What does it mean?

603
00:43:08,625 --> 00:43:10,655
Your nagging tone
when you chew someone out.

604
00:43:10,785 --> 00:43:13,905
Have they never
covered this in school?

605
00:43:15,425 --> 00:43:18,544
No... never heard it before.

606
00:43:18,545 --> 00:43:19,865
Is it even Thai?

607
00:43:25,685 --> 00:43:28,865
See... that makes it fun.

608
00:43:48,675 --> 00:43:49,675
You find it fun?

609
00:43:52,185 --> 00:43:53,185
Hmm...

610
00:43:54,495 --> 00:43:56,385
You wanna get AI to help?

611
00:43:57,505 --> 00:43:58,505
Let who help?

612
00:43:58,905 --> 00:43:59,905
AI.

613
00:44:00,235 --> 00:44:01,905
It's an app on the phone.

614
00:44:02,665 --> 00:44:04,865
Can I borrow your phone?

615
00:44:12,405 --> 00:44:13,645
Thank you.

616
00:44:27,675 --> 00:44:28,785
Hello.

617
00:44:30,865 --> 00:44:33,535
"Hello. How can I help you today?"

618
00:44:37,745 --> 00:44:40,385
Help me write a fun BL novel.

619
00:44:40,905 --> 00:44:42,305
"What novel did you say?"

620
00:44:47,385 --> 00:44:48,545
A gay novel.

621
00:44:51,485 --> 00:44:53,624
"I'm sorry. You like gay content?"

622
00:44:53,625 --> 00:44:55,065
Huh... no!

623
00:44:55,695 --> 00:44:58,025
No. You don't understand me.

624
00:45:01,945 --> 00:45:03,625
Good. Serves you right.

625
00:45:09,965 --> 00:45:11,705
Ta-da.

626
00:45:14,265 --> 00:45:16,465
Mabel and Yoyo are here
to give feedback today.

627
00:45:19,055 --> 00:45:20,055
Mm-hmm.

628
00:45:36,725 --> 00:45:39,865
This paragraph reads a lot like
"Sick Crush on My Senior."

629
00:45:41,545 --> 00:45:44,225
That part is just like
"Phi Nuea, My Undoing."

630
00:45:46,615 --> 00:45:48,665
Did you yoink from other novels?

631
00:45:49,255 --> 00:45:50,375
What does yoink mean?

632
00:45:50,945 --> 00:45:53,105
You lifted it
from someone else's work.

633
00:45:53,655 --> 00:45:55,925
I didn't lift anything.
It's just that...

634
00:45:57,065 --> 00:45:58,385
I had AI help me.

635
00:46:00,835 --> 00:46:02,515
That's not okay, Grandpa.

636
00:46:04,305 --> 00:46:05,305
Hmm?

637
00:46:15,325 --> 00:46:19,925
"Guy: Home yet? Not reading
my texts? Taking a dump?"

638
00:46:21,345 --> 00:46:23,615
"Save: Hey..."

639
00:46:33,705 --> 00:46:34,705
Save.

640
00:46:35,205 --> 00:46:36,205
Yeah?

641
00:46:37,095 --> 00:46:38,485
Oh, whew.

642
00:46:39,695 --> 00:46:41,455
Getting ready to be fried?

643
00:46:42,235 --> 00:46:43,235
Not funny.

644
00:46:43,265 --> 00:46:45,744
Fetch me field trip permission slips
from Grandpa's room

645
00:46:45,745 --> 00:46:47,025
and hand them out to the kids.

646
00:46:48,875 --> 00:46:49,875
Sure.

647
00:47:41,265 --> 00:47:44,465
"Demand for Repayment
and Notice of Legal Action."

648
00:47:49,355 --> 00:47:51,415
"Balance: 530 baht."

649
00:48:17,775 --> 00:48:20,665
Told you it wouldn't work.

650
00:48:21,295 --> 00:48:25,005
You complain a lot,
and it doesn't help anything.

651
00:48:25,305 --> 00:48:29,665
It's the truth.
This kind of sweet is out of style.

652
00:48:30,345 --> 00:48:32,225
All that money down the drain.

653
00:48:32,665 --> 00:48:34,344
At least we tried

654
00:48:34,345 --> 00:48:36,985
to save the house
from getting repossessed.

655
00:48:38,325 --> 00:48:40,504
This place is home to these kids.

656
00:48:40,505 --> 00:48:42,945
A lot of them
have nowhere else to go.

657
00:48:43,005 --> 00:48:44,865
We're the only family they have.

658
00:49:44,145 --> 00:49:45,665
Phi Save, play with us.

659
00:49:47,065 --> 00:49:49,025
Yeah, I'll be right there.

660
00:49:49,305 --> 00:49:50,465
Hurry up.

661
00:49:51,345 --> 00:49:52,345
Mm-hmm.

662
00:49:55,325 --> 00:49:57,185
- Ball.
- Yeah, catch.

663
00:50:01,665 --> 00:50:05,025
How are you, Jingjai?
Wanna play with your friends?

664
00:50:05,155 --> 00:50:07,225
Come. I will take you.

665
00:50:08,525 --> 00:50:10,545
That's it, sweetheart.

666
00:50:10,815 --> 00:50:12,905
Your friends are drawing something.

667
00:50:50,385 --> 00:50:51,385
Grandpa...

668
00:50:52,505 --> 00:50:53,945
How's the novel coming along?

669
00:50:55,025 --> 00:50:57,825
Snow read it. Not feeling it.

670
00:50:58,855 --> 00:51:00,825
The boy-boy energy just isn't there.

671
00:51:01,385 --> 00:51:05,545
Beats me. I've never once
been in love with a man.

672
00:51:06,725 --> 00:51:10,465
And none of my friends
have ever been that way either.

673
00:51:18,105 --> 00:51:19,105
Grandpa.

674
00:51:19,525 --> 00:51:22,975
You think your BL novel
will pay off our debt?

675
00:51:27,145 --> 00:51:28,145
What debt?

676
00:51:29,225 --> 00:51:31,704
Grandpa, you don't have to
hide it from me anymore.

677
00:51:31,705 --> 00:51:32,825
I know what's going on.

678
00:51:34,615 --> 00:51:37,905
Don't sweat it.
Leave it to the adults.

679
00:51:38,625 --> 00:51:41,785
Grandpa, I'm a grown-up now.
Just tell me.

680
00:51:42,425 --> 00:51:46,065
You think your BL novel
will save this house?

681
00:51:51,275 --> 00:51:52,275
Of course.

682
00:51:53,445 --> 00:51:55,505
I am an award-winning writer,
you know?

683
00:51:55,905 --> 00:51:58,665
It's just that
I still can't figure out...

684
00:51:59,345 --> 00:52:02,345
what it actually feels like
when a man loves a man.

685
00:52:04,025 --> 00:52:05,345
I know I can do it.

686
00:52:29,975 --> 00:52:31,425
You just add them up.

687
00:52:33,005 --> 00:52:34,465
That's how you get these values.

688
00:52:39,305 --> 00:52:40,305
We talk.

689
00:52:48,045 --> 00:52:49,045
What do you want?

690
00:52:50,065 --> 00:52:51,225
I need to talk to you.

691
00:52:51,505 --> 00:52:53,825
What more do you want from me?
I already backed away.

692
00:53:02,185 --> 00:53:03,185
Guy.

693
00:53:04,465 --> 00:53:05,745
How about we give this a try?

694
00:53:15,975 --> 00:53:18,944
What? You're seeing a boy?

695
00:53:18,945 --> 00:53:19,975
Hey, Grandpa.

696
00:53:19,995 --> 00:53:22,195
Don't tell Mom and Dad.

697
00:53:22,835 --> 00:53:24,985
Keep this between us.

698
00:53:25,165 --> 00:53:27,425
When you held hands,
did your heart race?

699
00:53:27,705 --> 00:53:30,865
Not at all. More like a jolt.

700
00:53:30,895 --> 00:53:32,305
I can't write this.

701
00:53:33,265 --> 00:53:35,504
I just... can't write this...

702
00:53:35,505 --> 00:53:41,504
The world keeps
turning every day.

703
00:53:41,505 --> 00:53:46,984
And we keep turning in its play.

704
00:53:46,985 --> 00:53:50,065
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

705
00:53:50,345 --> 00:53:52,825
We just might see
the world within.

706
00:53:52,855 --> 00:53:56,944
Let's walk together, day by day.

707
00:53:56,945 --> 00:54:01,785
Come take the step,
what do you say?

708
00:54:08,425 --> 00:54:12,184
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

709
00:54:12,185 --> 00:54:15,944
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

710
00:54:15,945 --> 00:54:20,944
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

711
00:54:20,945 --> 00:54:23,504
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

712
00:54:23,505 --> 00:54:26,184
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

713
00:54:26,185 --> 00:54:31,025
And land where
our hearts both grow.

714
00:54:31,345 --> 00:54:37,264
The world keeps
turning every day.

715
00:54:37,265 --> 00:54:42,584
And we keep turning in its play.

716
00:54:42,585 --> 00:54:45,825
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

717
00:54:46,105 --> 00:54:48,544
We just might see
the world within.

718
00:54:48,545 --> 00:54:52,624
Let's walk together, day by day.

719
00:54:52,625 --> 00:54:57,785
Come take the step,
what do you say?

